OL,3,CJersey public spending increased by
OL,4,C#146 million in 2023
OL,6,FA report into the States of Jersey
OL,7,FPublic Accounts has found that costs
OL,8,Fhave risen by #146 million in 2023,
OL,9,Fcompared to 2022.
OL,11,FThe annual review found that an extra
OL,12,F#83 million was spent on health
OL,13,Fservices while the cost of staffing
OL,14,Fincreased by #72 million.
OL,16,FThe main objective of the report was
OL,17,Fto investigate whether public funds
OL,18,Fhave been used in the way intended by
OL,19,Fthe States and whether financial
OL,20,Fpractices have been maintained.
