OL,3,CJersey public spending increased by
OL,4,C#146 million in 2023
OL,6,FThe review disclosed that the spend in
OL,7,F2023 within Health and Community
OL,8,FServices was #330 million, an increase
OL,9,Fof #83 million from 2022 when the
OL,10,Fspend was #247 million.
OL,12,FThe attributing factors are thought to
OL,13,Fbe increased pay awards in 2023, drug
OL,14,Finflation and a reliance on agency
OL,15,Fstaff along with additional overtime
OL,16,Fpayments for staff.
OL,18,FAn estimated #14 to #15 million has
OL,19,Fbeen predicted to have been spent on
OL,20,FHealth and Community Services Agency
OL,21,Fstaff costs within 2024.
