OL,3,CJersey public spending increased by
OL,4,C#146 million in 2023
OL,6,FHowever, the report has stated that
OL,7,Fthe Financial Recovery Plan within
OL,8,FHealth and Community Services is
OL,9,Ffocused over a three-year period and
OL,10,Fintends to achieve savings.
OL,12,FIt's hoped that money will be saved
OL,13,Fthrough a reduction of agency staff
OL,14,Fand improvements in procurement
OL,15,Fprocesses.
OL,17,FAlong with the concerns around
OL,18,Fstaffing costs and funds for health
OL,19,Fdepartments, the report mentions the
OL,20,Fneed to offer more training on-island
OL,21,Fto highlight key recruitment gaps.
